        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:44PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Canaan, or 17 miles northwest of Ripley, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rogers Springs, Canaan, Saulsbury, Chalybeate, Snow Lake Shores,
Brody, Pocahontas, Lisbon, New Canaan, Lacy, Essary Springs,
Brownfield, Walnut, Michigan City, Lone Pine, Hebron, Hamilton,
Middleton, Big Hill Pond State Park, and Tiplersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northeastern
and northwestern Mississippi...and west Tennessee.</instruction>
